# Example baked-secrets file for the OPD .sif build.
#
# Copy to `opd_secrets.env` (same dir as the .def) and fill in REAL values, then run build_opd_sif.sh.
# Format: plain KEY=VALUE, one per line. NO `export`, NO quotes — the DEF's %environment loop parses it
# raw. Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored. All three keys are required (the build guard checks them).
#
# SECURITY: opd_secrets.env is gitignored and must never be committed. The built .sif carries these live
# credentials — keep it local (the NII transfer only), never push it to a shared/public registry.

HF_TOKEN=hf_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
WANDB_API_KEY=xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
